{%- comment -%}
  Inline, hidden SVG sprite — rendered once in layout/theme.liquid, right after <body>
  opens. Every icon in the theme is referenced elsewhere via snippets/icon.liquid,
  which points a <use> at one of these <symbol> ids. Inlining (rather than loading a
  separate icons.svg asset and referencing it cross-file) avoids the <use>
  cross-origin/caching quirks older Safari has with external SVG sprites, at the cost
  of a few hundred bytes duplicated in the initial HTML — a good trade for a sprite
  this small (spec §12: "icons as inline SVG sprite, no icon font").

  Icons are sourced from Lucide (ISC license) and kept at their 1.5px-stroke
  "Lucide-style discipline" (spec §5.5) rather than Lucide's own 2px default.
  Only icons actually consumed by a shipped component belong here — add new
  <symbol> entries only when a real caller needs them, not speculatively.

  Current consumers (Milestone 2):
    icon-plus         — accordion toggle (rotates 45° into a close glyph), quantity increase,
                        and reused rotated 45° wherever a plain "×" dismiss/close glyph is
                        needed (spec has no separate close icon — one glyph, two jobs)
    icon-minus        — quantity decrease
    icon-chevron-down — custom select chevron; reused rotated ±90° for chevron-left/right
                        (mobile nav submenu disclosure / back button) instead of two more symbols
    icon-check        — checkbox checked glyph, field success state
    icon-circle-alert — field error state

  Added in Milestone 3 (header/nav):
    icon-search, icon-user, icon-shopping-bag, icon-heart, icon-git-compare, icon-menu

  Added in Milestone 4 (commerce components):
    icon-eye  — quick view trigger
    icon-star — rating placeholder (stroke-only; add class="icon--filled" for a
                filled star rather than adding a second symbol)

  Added in Milestone 5 (homepage):
    icon-pause, icon-play — video hero pause/play control

  Added in Milestone 6 (collection experience):
    icon-sliders-horizontal — filter toggle
    icon-grid-2x2, icon-grid-3x3, icon-layout-grid — grid column switcher (2/3/4)
    icon-x — active-filter chip removal (a dedicated glyph rather than the
             rotated-plus reuse, since chips are small/frequent enough that a
             purpose-drawn × reads more cleanly at that size)

  Added in Milestone 7 (product experience):
    icon-maximize — gallery zoom/expand trigger
    icon-share-2  — share button
    icon-truck, icon-rotate-ccw, icon-shield-check, icon-lock — trust badge rows
             (shipping, returns, warranty, secure). Gallery/lightbox prev-next
             arrows reuse icon-chevron-down + the existing .icon--rotate-90 /
             .icon--rotate-neg90 utilities (same convention as mobile-nav's
             back/forward chevrons) rather than adding two more symbols.

  Added in Milestone 10 (blog, customer accounts, contact):
    icon-mail, icon-phone, icon-map-pin — contact page store-info rows
    icon-eye-off — account login/register password visibility toggle
             (paired with the existing icon-eye for the "shown" state)
    icon-message-circle — article comment count/section heading
    icon-instagram, icon-facebook, icon-x-social, icon-youtube, icon-tiktok,
    icon-pinterest — contact page social links. Article prev/next nav and
    the blog tag-filter "clear" affordance reuse icon-chevron-down (rotated)
    and icon-x exactly as already established, no new symbols needed.
{%- endcomment -%}
